headline: Mastercard beats profit estimates as transaction volumes hold strong
summary: Consumer spending has proven resilient, while labor market cracks and sticky inflation continue to fuel concerns over U.S. President Donald Trump's trade and immigration policies.  Mastercard's earnings round off the earnings season for card companies, which are closely tracked by Wall Street to gauge consumer health.  Due to their expansive share of global everyday transactions, card networks run by Mastercard and Visa are widely perceived as shielded from a potential payments slowdown.
